The paper deals with the problem of transmitting a Gaussian source over a Gaussian channel, which is a classic problem in information theory and signal processing. The paper proposes a novel scheme that combines prediction and modulo-lattice operations to achieve optimal performance, which is a topic of interest in the areas of information theory, multimedia, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
